    <p>(Soundbite of cheering crowd) </p>
    <p>Mr. ROMNEY: Thank you, Wyoming. </p>
    <p>LIASSON: Although fewer independents voted in the Republican primary than the Democratic primary, McCain got the lion's share of their votes. He split support of Republicans with Romney. McCain also did better among the half of Republican voters who were unhappy with President Bush. Romney carried those who were satisfied with the president. </p>
