    <p>Ms. GILBERT: She did. She was 377 to Obama's 343.  </p>
    <p>WERTHEIMER: It's much closer in Jaffrey. </p>
    <p>Ms. GILBERT: It is, only by two votes. </p>
    <p>WERTHEIMER: And as the evening went on, it began to look that as Jaffrey voted, so would the whole state vote, giving a narrow victory to Hillary Clinton.  </p>
