    <p>Ms. ANNE WEBB: All of a sudden, on Saturday morning, I woke up and I thought, well, I don't know why, if I like all of these people equally, I think it's all right not to vote for Hillary. And so I woke up on Saturday morning thinking I have to vote for Hillary; women in this country are never recognized for what they accomplish or what they say. And I must not fall into the trap of not acknowledging her contribution to government in this country.  </p>
    <p>Unidentified Man #1: She's winning, 48 percent.  </p>
